throwHardExceptionInThread(RuntimeException, Thread) - Static method in class ej.bon.Util
Throws an exception in a specified thread.
If the thread is either sleeping or waiting, the thread is unblocked and the exception is thrown as soon as possible. If the thread is running, the exception is thrown just as if a throw statement was the next instruction to execute. If the thread is not started yet or is terminated, nothing is done. If the thread has entered one or more critical sections, it does not wait the critical sections to finish and the exception is thrown as soon as possible. If an exception thrown via Util.throwHardExceptionInThread(RuntimeException, Thread) is already pending for the thread, nothing is done. If an exception thrown via Util.throwExceptionInThread(RuntimeException, Thread) is already pending for the thread, this exception is replaced by the given exception.
